IWAS (International Wheelchair and Amputees Spors Federation)  - An international sports organization that govern the athlete with disability. Iwas headquartered is at Stoke Mandeville Stadium, Stoke Mandeville, Buckinghamshire, and is a registered charity.

INAS-FID (International Sports Federation for Person with Intellectual Disability) -Was established in 1986, by professionals in Netherland, who were involved in sport and wanted to promote participation for athletes with mental handicap to elite sports.

CP-ISRA (Cerebral Palsy International Sports and Recreation Association) - The CP-ISRA sports are open to the athlete with cerebral palsy and athlete who had similar disability resulting from  the nuerogical disorder such as stroke or traumatic brain injury (TBI)
IBSA (International Blind Sport Federation) - The IBSA sports Administrations System are designed to support and facilitate the infromation management of the person with disabilities.

- To promote general interest and welfare for the disable in the region through the participation of sport events and other activities -To deepen mutual undertanding and friendship of the disabled -To promote rehabilitation for the disable through sport activities
